value.title: Trump and McConnell's Supreme Court plan justifies anything the Democrats do in 2021
value.excerpt: Packing the court, ending the filibuster and giving Washington, D.C. and Puerto Rico statehood should all be on the table, if all norms are off the table.

value.title: Maya Rudolph wins Emmy as Kamala Harris; Jason Bateman given Ron Cephas Jones' award
value.excerpt: Maya Rudolph won a Creative Arts Emmy for her "SNL" role as Kamala Harris, and a ceremony gaffe crowned Jason Bateman instead of Ron Cephas Jones.

value.title: GOP's Scott, Baker don't want Trump to fill Supreme Court vacancy before election
value.excerpt: "The Supreme Court is too important to rush and must be removed from partisan political infighting," Gov. Charlie Baker wrote.

value.title: Hillary Clinton says McConnell, Trump move to confirm Ginsburg successor shows 'lust for power'
value.excerpt: The former Democratic president and former Democratic presidential nominee weighed in on the fight over the seat of the late Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg

value.title: Trump tells supporters 'you'll never see me again' if he loses to Biden
value.excerpt: Trump made similar remarks in 2016, saying, "I don't think I'm going to lose, but if I do, I don't think you're ever going to see me again."

value.title: Judge delays Trump administration’s restrictions on messaging app WeChat
value.excerpt: In a ruling dated Saturday, a judge in California said the government’s actions would affect users' First Amendment rights as an effective ban on the app removes their platform for communication.

value.title: Bill Clinton: 'Superficially hypocritical' for Trump and Republicans to push to fill Supreme Court vacancy
value.excerpt: Former President Bill Clinton said Sunday it is "superficially hypocritical" for President Donald Trump and Senate Republicans to push to put a new justice on the Supreme Court before the November election.

value.title: Pelosi won't rule out new impeachment to delay SCOTUS vote if Biden wins
value.excerpt: "Well, we have our options," Pelosi told ABC's "This Week." "We have arrows in our quiver that I’m not about to discuss right now."

value.title: Joe Biden headed to Manitowoc Monday for second Wisconsin visit
value.excerpt: Joe Biden’s campaign announced Sunday that the Democratic presidential nominee would be campaigning in Manitowoc, a city of about 32,000 about 80 miles north of Milwaukee.

value.title: Students are in a lose-lose situation during the pandemic, and Trump is to blame
value.excerpt: Trump's leadership during the pandemic has left students stuck between a rock and a hard place. Joe Biden has the skills necessary to succeed.

value.title: Computing pioneers endorse Biden, citing Trump immigration crackdown
value.excerpt: Two dozen award-winning computer scientists, in a rebuke of President Donald Trump’s immigration policies, said Friday that they were endorsing Joe Biden in November’s presidential election.

value.title: Trump remains the underdog as campaign enters final six-week stretch
value.excerpt: This year has felt anything but stable in most aspects of American life, but the presidential campaign of 2020 has been bucking that dynamic and has proven to be remarkably stable for the last several months.

value.title: What California’s COVID approach could teach the country if Joe Biden wins
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential candidate Joe Biden and California Gov. Gavin Newsom share the same basic COVID-19 philosophy: The government must focus on fighting the virus before the economy can recover.

value.title: Analysis: Trump's race-baiting might come at a cost to his economy
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump's increasingly naked race-baiting heading into the final stretch of the 2020 campaign suggests he shares the consensus explanation for his grip on White working-class voters: it's about their racial resentments, not their economic anxieties.

value.title: Joe Biden uses Supreme Court vacancy to argue that 'health care hangs in balance’ for voters in November election
value.excerpt: Joe Biden on Sunday used the Supreme Court vacancy to reinforce his argument that the election should be a referendum on President Donald Trump’s handling of health care.

value.title: China is our greatest foreign policy issue. But neither Trump nor Biden have it right.
value.excerpt: Xi Jinping's China is fundamentally different from the past. Neither Donald Trump's nor Joe Biden's approach fully responds to that new reality.

value.title: AOC warns libs Trump-Biden election a lifestyle changer: ‘There’s no going back to brunch’
value.excerpt: Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez has braced her supporters for a very different future than they may have expected -- even if presidential nominee Joe Biden and other Democrats prevail in November.

value.title: Trump backs proposed deal to keep TikTok operating in US
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump says he’s given his “blessing” to a proposed deal that would see the popular video-sharing app TikTok partner with Oracle and Walmart and form a U.S. company

value.title: Biden takes cautious approach to SCOTUS storm
value.excerpt: His campaign is laying plans to shift the focus of the looming Supreme Court nomination fight toward a referendum on the Affordable Care Act.

value.title: Trump eyes Cuban American judge from Florida for Supreme Court
value.excerpt: Barbara Lagoa would bring lengthy judicial experience and two potential political benefits: She is a Cuban American from a battleground state.

value.title: Oracle announces it will become a minority investor in TikTok Global after Trump indicates his approval
value.excerpt: The news is the latest development in the saga of TikTok, the viral video app which was pressured into selling itself to a US-based company.

value.title: Kamala Harris pays tribute to RBG with Supreme Court pic
value.excerpt: Democratic Vice Presidential candidate Kamala Harris paid tribute to the passing of Supreme Court Justice Ruth Bader Ginsberg Saturday, calling the liberal icon a “titan.”

value.title: Donald Trump Target Of Ricin Poisoned Letter For Second Time
value.excerpt: A letter containing the poison Ricin was intercepted before arrival on President Donald Trump’s desk for the second time, according to law enforcement officials. The New York Times reports that a package containing the poison and addressed to the President was intercepted earlier this week and is undergoing investigation by both the FBI and the Secret Service.

value.title: Trump Describes Journalist Hit By Rubber Bullet ‘A Beautiful Sight’
value.excerpt: At a rally in Minnesota, President Trump described an MSNBC anchor hit by a rubber bullet while covering protests after the death of George Floyd in May as “a beautiful sight,” comments quickly condemned by journalists including CNN’s Jake Tapper.
